<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-415-778  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 415 778.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  May 7 1990 v24 n19 p112(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sterling tools bridge IBM gap. (Sterling Software Inc. introducesmodular Storage Automation Management System suite of datamanagement software modules) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bozman, Jean S.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Sterling Software Inc introduces Storage Automation ManagementSystem (SAMS), a suite of modular data-management programs thatcombine graphical user interfaces with artificial intelligencealgorithms to provide transparent disk drive usage.andP;  SAMS isdesigned to complement IBM's system managed storage (SMS) design,providing features the computer giant has not yet addressed.andP;  Itenhances the IBM architecture with real-time query support, anicon-based system for displaying disk drive utilization data, andAutomatic Initiation Manager (AIM), which dynamically reallocatesmemory space.andP;  SAMS is built on Sterling's venerable DMS/OSdata-management system, which is already running on many IBMmainframes.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sterling Software Inc. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    SSW.andO;Product:   Storage Automation Management System (Utility program) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Software packagesProduct IntroductionModularityData ManagementUser Interface.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>